```plantuml
@startuml adityajain10_foot365-live-streaming-chatbot-prediction-app-on-aws

actor User
participant Frontend as "Frontend (HTML/JS)"
participant APIGateway as "API Gateway"
participant LambdaStandings as "Lambda\n(standings.py)"
participant LambdaPredictions as "Lambda\n(predictions.py)"
participant LambdaChatbot as "Lambda\n(LF1.py/LF2.py)"
participant LambdaFixtures as "Lambda\n(getFixtures.py)"
participant LambdaScores as "Lambda\n(getScore.py/getLiveScores.py)"
participant DynamoDB
participant ElasticSearch
participant SageMaker
participant SQS
participant SNS
participant Lex as "Lex Chatbot"

User -> Frontend: Accesses match data/predictions/chat
Frontend -> APIGateway: GET/POST requests
APIGateway -> LambdaStandings: Fetch standings
LambdaStandings -> DynamoDB: Query match data
DynamoDB --> LambdaStandings: Return standings
LambdaStandings --> APIGateway: Response
APIGateway --> Frontend: Display standings

Frontend -> APIGateway: Request predictions
APIGateway -> LambdaPredictions: Trigger prediction
LambdaPredictions -> SageMaker: Invoke ML model
SageMaker --> LambdaPredictions: Prediction results
LambdaPredictions --> APIGateway: Return predictions
APIGateway --> Frontend: Display predictions

User -> Frontend: Interacts with chatbot
Frontend -> Lex: Send user message
Lex -> LambdaChatbot: Process intent
LambdaChatbot -> ElasticSearch: Query fixtures
ElasticSearch --> LambdaChatbot: Return matches
LambdaChatbot -> SQS: Enqueue request (if async)
SQS -> LambdaChatbot: Dequeue for processing
LambdaChatbot -> SNS: Send SMS notification
LambdaChatbot --> Lex: Bot response
Lex --> Frontend: Display chatbot reply

Frontend -> APIGateway: Request live scores
APIGateway -> LambdaScores: Fetch scores
LambdaScores -> ElasticSearch: Get match IDs
ElasticSearch --> LambdaScores: Return IDs
LambdaScores -> DynamoDB: Query live data
DynamoDB --> LambdaScores: Return scores
LambdaScores --> APIGateway: Response
APIGateway --> Frontend: Update live scores

@enduml
```